This year’s Open Day at the All-India Institute of Speech and Hearing (AIISH) will educate visitors, especially the youth, on issues related to disability.The event, scheduled on January 29 from 9.30 a.m. to 4 p.m, is open to all.The theme of this year’s event is ‘Hearing Protection’. An exhibition has been arranged at the Knowledge Park of the institute to educate schoolchildren and visitors on hearing mechanism, speech production, prevention and management of communication disorders, harmful effects of noise, and vocal hygiene. Competitions such as debate, painting, and quiz on speech and hearing will be held for high school and college students. Games such as maths and memory, word recognition, rebounce ball, challenge your reading, and bursting balloons have also been arranged.Multiple games will be held for children with special needs and their caretakers.For children with hearing impairment, events such as treasure hunt, cap race, mala making race, lemon and spoon race, and balloon blowing will be conducted. For children with mental disabilities, passing the ball, softball throw, running race, lemon race, musical chair will be held.Heads of schools and colleges who wish to send students to participate in the competitions can call 8884047032 or 9620004490 for more details.This year’s event will educate visitors, especially youth, on issues related to disability